(3/4) The OPD Crisis Negotiators were able to talk Jacobs safely out of the house at 6:40 AM. He was taken into custody without further incident. Jacobs has been charged with domestic violence – aggravated assault and is currently awaiting a bond hearing.

(2/4) Around 2:00 AM, the suspect, Jodie Jacobs (36 of Oxford, MS) was located at his residence at Countryview Village off of Anchorage Road. Officers set up around the house and began negotiating his safe surrender.

(1/4) On Monday, December 16, 2019, at approximately 1:30 AM, officers with OPD responded to the ER at Baptist Memorial Hospital – North Mississippi for a person who had a non-life threatening gunshot wound.

It usually goes until around 8 o'clock.

If you drive on Van Buren Ave. towards the Square, you will be redirected onto the South 11th St. alley next to the Library to Jackson Ave. If you come up East Jackson towards the Square, you will be redirected onto North 13th St. North Lamar will be blocked off at Price St.

If you are coming up University towards the Square during the parade, you will be redirected onto S. 13th behind Bancorp South Bank. If you are coming up South Lamar towards the Square, you will be redirected onto Taylor Avenue.

Traffic in the lineup staging area on University, between 5th and Old Taylor, will be shut down starting at 3PM. The other blocked off areas for the parade route will be shut down as the parade begins at 6:30.

Tonight at 6:30 is the annual Christmas Parade! Here is a map marking the parade route. The parade will start on University Ave. between 5th and Old Taylor and end at the new activity center on Price Street.pic.twitter.com/T1zwxLb0Hd
